cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Verify-or-Trust, please cite it as below."
title: "Verify-or-Trust: a verifiable-reward agentic benchmark for biology foundation-model orchestration"
authors:
  - family-names: Kim
    given-names: Jihoon
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-06-12
license: Apache-2.0
abstract: >
  Verify-or-Trust measures whether an LLM agent, orchestrating a fallible perturbation foundation model,
  allocates costly verification (a real differential-expression assay) to the genes where the model is actually
  wrong. Graded by a held-out real experiment (a verifiable reward), with LLM-free baselines, two substrates
  (GEARS/Norman, Arc STATE/Tahoe), and genuine tool execution.
